					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>On a wall in front of the same cave.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Māṟavarmaṉ Sundara-pāṇḍyadēva (I): Year 15+1 = 1231-32 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This record is much damaged. It describes the king as <hi rend="italic">Śōṇāḍu-koṇḍu Muḍikoṇḍaśōḻapurattu vīrābhishēkamum paṇṇiyaruḷiya.</hi></p>						

						<p>It seems to record a gift of land in Niyamam for food offerings to god Tēnāṟṟu-Nāyakar by Gaṇḍan Udaiyañcheydāṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Gāṅgēyaṉ of Niyamam, one of the villages irrigated by (the river) Tēnāṟu in Kēraḷasiṅga-vaḷanāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
